<div id="review_1293642702" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1293642702" />
    <a title="Mayank Pandya" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41009108-mayank-pandya"><img alt="Mayank Pandya" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1425819127p2/41009108.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1293642702?book_show_action=true">May 29, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mayank Pandya" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mayank Pandya" href="/user/show/41009108-mayank-pandya">Mayank Pandya</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1293642702" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14511492512753732468">This book is must read for all Indian, especially those concerned with issues of Hindu society. The amount of research behind this book is praiseworthy and is an eye opener that Indians should now rise above the petty local politics and think in national terms.<br/><br/>I recommend this book to every India who is interested in national politics, and wants to understand Indian policies and how they are shaped in response to West. This book shows the true face of many important figures who appear regularly </span>
  <span id="freeText14511492512753732468" style="display:none">This book is must read for all Indian, especially those concerned with issues of Hindu society. The amount of research behind this book is praiseworthy and is an eye opener that Indians should now rise above the petty local politics and think in national terms.<br /><br />I recommend this book to every India who is interested in national politics, and wants to understand Indian policies and how they are shaped in response to West. This book shows the true face of many important figures who appear regularly on national channels and their true political intentions.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14511492512753732468" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


